{
  "stem": "23090.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The-- the-- the number of people remained the same because we were not dislodged since we lived there before the war-- the war, and [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] we-- we basically lived-- there was the same amount of people till we left the ghetto as we did before.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So there was my family, my sister, and myself, my dad, and an aunt-- a sister of my mother's who was with us prior to the warr-- also.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The typical day is something that-- you get up in the morning, you [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] go to work.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, we didn't daven.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- we didn't daven.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And go to work, and you're hungry.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, when you're hungry, that's-- your typical day begins when you're hungry and your typical day ends when you're hungry.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When you're not hungry, you think of things to do and-- other than that-- other than just that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so, since I was always hungry, my day always began with being hungry and couldn't wait until I eat the next time and the next time.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] You were observing things that you'd sort of become almost oblivious to, that would shock you some other time.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You see now people laying on the street from starvation, from hunger.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You see death of someone is becoming a very common and normal [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] acceptance.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Death, in fact, just becomes a matter of fact thing on a daily basis.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sickness is prevalent, like common knowledge.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's everywhere.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you hear rumors and you hear conversation of nothing but the end-- the end of everything.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And what do we need to live?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And what is there left?",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
